### 🟡 MEDIUM — Eager Test

**Test:** `OrderProcessor_FullWorkflow_Succeeds` (line 52)

```csharp
processor.ValidateOrder(order);
processor.CalculateTotal(order);
processor.ApplyDiscount(order, "SAVE10");
processor.ReserveInventory(order);
processor.ProcessPayment(order, new CreditCard("4111111111111111"));
processor.SendConfirmation(order);
processor.UpdateOrderHistory(order);
Assert.AreEqual("Completed", order.Status);
```

Seven distinct production method calls. If this test fails, you have no idea which step broke. The single assertion at the end only checks the final status, leaving all intermediate behavior unverified.

**Fix:** Either break into focused tests per step, or if this is intentionally an integration/workflow test, rename it and add intermediate assertions:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void ProcessOrder_EndToEnd_CompletesFullWorkflow()
{
    // If intentionally an integration test, add per-step assertions:
    processor.ValidateOrder(order);
    Assert.AreEqual("Validated", order.Status);

    processor.CalculateTotal(order);
    Assert.IsTrue(order.TotalAmount > 0);
    // ... etc.
}
```

