## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Test(s) | Effort | Why First |
|----------|-------|---------|--------|-----------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free | `CompletesWithoutError` | Low | False-pass risk — this test verifies nothing |
| 2 | Conditional Logic | `SetsCorrectStatus` | Low | Hidden gap — one branch is never tested |
| 3 | Mystery Guest | `ImportOrders_FromCsv` | Low | Broken in CI — test can't run anywhere but one machine |
| 4 | Sleepy Test | `AsyncNotification_IsSent` | Medium | Top flakiness predictor |
| 5 | Exception Handling | `EmptyOrder_ThrowsValidationError` | Low | Quick swap to `ThrowsException<T>` |
| 6 | Magic Numbers | `CalculateTotal` | Low | Add named constants + assertion messages |
| 7 | Sensitive Equality | `GetOrderSummary` | Medium | Assert on properties instead of `ToString()` |
| 8 | Eager Test | `FullWorkflow_Succeeds` | High | Needs decomposition or reclassification |
| 9 | General Fixture | Class-wide `_logger` | Low | Remove unused field |

Fixes 1–3 and 5–6 are one-liners or small rewrites. Tackling those first eliminates the false-pass and environment-coupling risks with minimal effort.
